Class description:
ABT circuit workout routine is the perfect workout for a quick lower
body burn. This workout routine can be easily done with or without
equipment. As the name says, we are working on toning your core,
butt and thigh muscles. Are you ready for the burn?

Aerobics is a form of rhythmic dance exercise. Instructors will teach one step or movement at a time and start building up from there into a whole choreography. Movements are very easy to follow, repetitive and fun!

A low-impact aerobic exercise conducted in a swimming pool (not covering the head), uses water as a form of resistance or assistance. It reduces joint pressure, increases flexibility, and builds endurance. No swimming experience required

Barre is a combination of yoga, pilates, strength training, and ballet techniques that works out the entire body. It focuses on isometric holds and combines dynamic movements to tone and sculpt the body. Suitable for all fitness levels, participants can embrace their inner ballerina and get a full-body workout at the same time. Individuals will attain better body awareness, and improve physical strength, flexibility and posture.

An artistic and creative way of working with the body, merging strength, flexibility, and breathing techniques to strengthen and stretch muscles, relieve tension, improve posture, and better understand our bodies. It is inspired by yoga, pilates, functional training, and tai chi techniques.
A combination of Bollywood dancing with high-intensity cardio workout, involving the whole body, shaking to the Bollywood music as though you are in the movies!

Designed to build strength and fitness through a variety of high-intensity intervals and circuit training, Bootcamp/HIIT uses bodyweight exercises that can be regressed or progressed. As such, this makes it suitable for participants of all fitness levels to tone up their muscles and improve cardiovascular endurance.

A form of exercise consisting of a variety of movements that involve large muscle groups such as pull-ups, jumping, grasping, pushing, etc. It is often performed rhythmically with minimal equipment to increase strength and flexibility. Be amazed at what your body can do!
A combination of martial arts techniques with a fast-paced cardio workout, Cardio Kickboxing helps build stamina and improves coordination.

In this class, you will be guided on doing simple & easy stretches that can be done at the desk whether you are in office wear, sportswear, or comfortable home clothes. This is one of our popular classes to have in the middle of the workday to reset your posture, release muscle tightness & feel more productive for the rest of the day.
Emerged from the music of Hip-Hop culture together with the evolution from the influences of pop culture, Hip Hop emphasizes groove, strength, and precision.

Dance along with to Kpop music while burning calories at the same time through a cardio-based workout that is suitable for people of all ages and dance experiences. Includes some essence of music video moves.
Freestyle dance inspired by Kpop music. Learn popular choreography from Kpop music videos from both girl bands and boy bands.

Inspired by catchy Kpop music videos, KpopX Fitness uses simplified Kpop dance moves together with aerobic and body toning exercises. Steps are easy to follow, making them suitable for anyone regardless of dance background.

Influenced by high-energy Bhangra and Bollywood Dance movements, it is an easy-to-follow fitness format which caters to people of all ages and fitness levels who wish to stay active with unique music and beats.
With a blend of pilates, yoga exercises, and rhythmic breathing, exercise along with a relaxing and mindful flow of uplifting music beats, while focussing on the flow of the body & mind.

Pilates mat work will guide the class through mobilizing the spine, improving core strength, and most importantly, increasing awareness of daily posture. It is gentle and friendly for people with knee or back pain as well.

A non-stop cardio fusion of standing Pilates, boxing, and dance to strengthen the core, sculpt the body and elongate the muscles. Move along to the music and beats to execute the techniques of boxing to get the heart pumping too.
Influenced by plyometrics, sports conditioning drills, and functional training, Piloxing Knockout increases fitness levels and builds endurance.

Inspired by commercial dance from Los Angeles, it is suitable for people of all fitness levels, ages, and backgrounds. Dance along to music hits and iconic throwbacks while learning the most  current grooves from LA’s dance scene
A form of exercise that involves exerting maximum force in short time intervals using jumping or explosive movements. Some examples include jump ropes, lunges, and jump squats.

A full-body workout that combines cardio, conditioning, and strength training with yoga and Pilates-inspired movements. Using lightly weighted drumsticks, transforms drumming into an effective way of working out.

A Latin-based dance workout with a strong focus on musicality and lyrical expression. It converts functional training protocols into innovative dance moves which are controlled and grounded, making it fun and sage at the same time.
Developed in response to the emergence of commercial pop music, it features sharp movements, and body isolations and focuses on precision and confidence.
STRONG Nation combines high-intensity interval training with the science of Synced Music Motivation. Imagine doing burpees at the beat of the music!

A series of gentle physical exercises and stretches. Each posture flows into the next without pause, ensuring that your body is in constant motion. Tai Chi promotes serenity through gentle movements — connecting the mind and body.
Yoga is a form of physical exercise to promote improved control of mind and body, exercise focussing on strength, flexibility, and breathing to boost physical and mental well-being.

Incorporating techniques from Latin dance styles alongside energetic soundtracks, Zumba is an aerobic workout that improves coordination and endurance. The intensity of the workout differs, depending on the type of class.
Modified Zumba class for active older individuals who want to reproduce their favorite moves at a lower intensity.
A pool party that incorporates the South American Zumba beat and dance steps. It's a water-based, body-toning workout that's both enjoyable and tough.
A high-energy dance party packed with kid-friendly routines where kids learn to move, listen to the rhythm, exercise their bodies, and improve their health while listening to their favorite music.

Resistance band training is one of the most cost-effective ways to work
on strength training, anytime, anywhere. Paired up with up-beat music,
the class can be full of energy, burning muscles, and fun! This class is
suitable for all ages and fitness levels as the band’s tightness can be
modified according to its length and thickness.
*Participants are required to own a set of resistance bands

Applicable in the comfort of the office or your own home, learn how to release tight muscle knots wherever you are with a massage ball, paired with stretching on a chair or standing at the desk to release tension in the whole body. Partner stretches can also be done between colleagues or family members as well to get a deeper stretch in.

Class title: Food as Fuel to Optimise Your Workout
Class description:
Your body needs the right fuel for you to perform at your best, and that’s where good nutritional strategies come into play to complement
your own fi tness plans. This talk provides an overview of sport nutrition, the relationship between food and humans, and what food does to the body at rest and
during exercise. It also discusses how different nutritional components are stored in the body and their functions during physical activities.

Abdominal pains, bloatedness, and bowel irregularities are common symptoms of poor gut health and surprisingly, early signs of diseases like eczema, colon cancer, or even anxiety. In this talk, we’ll discuss how food affects our gut, common imbalances that could arise, ways to relieve them, and practical tips to strengthen our gut health.

Class title: Food for Productivity: No more Food Comas
Class description: Food coma (aka after-meal sleepiness) is a leading cause of unproductiveness, especially after lunch hours. Learn how to choose the right foods throughout the day to prevent food comas, improve mental alertness, and increase energy levels for better productivity at work.

Ever wonder why you’re usually in a good mood after eating?
According to the latest scientifi c studies, the phrase “you are what you
eat” speaks to both our physical and emotional health. In this talk, we’ll
show you how the food we eat affects our bodies and minds, what
foods might cause dips and peaks in our mood, and tips to E.A.R.N. your
health and enhance your mood.

Is snacking good or bad for you? In this talk, we’ll show you the pros and cons of snacking, help you differentiate good and bad snacking
habits, and provide some easy tips to choose snacks that are good for your health, especially when you’re on a weight management journey.

Class title: The Silent Killers: Obesity, Diabetes, Stroke
Class description:
In recent years, more people are getting diagnosed with lifestyle diseases that became so severe, sudden death is a possible risk they
have to live with. In this talk, we’ll raise your awareness of the risk factors that can lead to lifestyle diseases, offer some key nutritional tips
to help you watch what you eat, and guard you against lifestyle habits that may just kill you silently.

How are men and women built differently? How does that affect our nutritional needs? In this talk, we’ll show you the differences in our
body systems and what it means for our eating and weight regulation behaviours. You’ll also learn some basic food nutrition for your unique
body, so you can make better food and lifestyle choices in the long term.

Class title: Nutrition for Women: Gut Health and Female Hormone
Class description:
There are some nutritional needs unique to females, and catering to them can mean the difference to the way you work, live, and play. In
this talk, we’ll offer some insight into the connection between gut health and female hormones, while offering some top tips to nourish the female body in the best ways.

We can’t stop our bodies from ageing but we defi nitely can adjust our diets to stay strong and healthy. In this talk, you’ll discover how ageing
affects our overall health and learn to make the right food choices in support of graceful ageing.

A well-functioning immune system is the foundation of good health that protects us against disease and infections. In this talk, you discover
the role of nutrition in building and maintaining a healthy immune system as we discuss the myths and facts around ‘Immunity-boosting
supplements’. You’ll also get to pick up some tips on choosing the right kind of food to keep illnesses at bay.

With so much confl icting information about diet plans out there, it’s hard knowing what will work in your case. In this talk, we’ll break down
the root causes of obesity and its consequences, so you can get familiar with what you’re really dealing with. You’ll also be provided with
actionable tips to achieve and maintain your ideal, healthy weight though food and lifestyle changes.

Eating out is also about discovering what’s out there to enjoy or to spend quality time with others, but that doesn’t mean your health
needs to take a back seat. In this talk, we’ll help you understand the importance of eating well, show you its benefits to our wellbeing, and
offer some practical steps to stay healthy even when eating out.

Tempted by a ‘quick fi x’ or ‘miracle’ weight loss? It’s probably too good to be true! Fad diets gained popularity by offering short-term weight
loss fast, but results with such minimal effort are often unrealistic and unsustainable. In this talk, we’ll cover why various fad diets seem
effective but may be unsustainable, so you can decide if they’re really worth it.

Prepare your meals in a more effective and effi cient manner while taking control of your nutrition through meal-prepping. In this talk, you’ll
discover the health tradeoffs you’re making when ordering takeouts, how easy having a homecooked, nutritious meal after work can really be, and
the various secrets to save time without losing out on taste while improving your food’s shelf life.

Learn to whip up yummy and healthy dishes from our nutritionist/dietician, all from the comfort of your home kitchen! We’ll
show you how to enhance your food with natural ingredients and pick healthier alternatives for common local recipes.
All you’ll need is your kitchen equipment and stove, fresh ingredients (we’ll share an ingredients list 2 weeks before the demo) and to follow
along on the day itself! Vegan and vegetarian options are available upon request.

Class title: Restart To Win: Getting back to work effectively
Class description: The COVID-19 health pandemic has resulted in numerous disruptions to our lives and the way we work. While governments and health agencies are learning how to cope and manage effectively, companies are eager to restart to ensure survivability of their respective businesses.

We live in a fast-paced and demanding society. Surmounting pressures from work demands can leave many people in Singapore with stress-related problems. Mental health is now a great concern, especially with about 1 in 10 adults suffering from mental illnesses in Singapore.
While it is impossible not to experience stress, early intervention and better-coping skills can signifi cantly reduce stress and mental health issues.

situations, and it is inevitable that we may react with anxiety to some of them. However, it is important to  differentiate ordinary anxiety from anxiety disorders.
During the recent COVID-19 outbreak, we have observed social phenomena such as hoarding, distancing, and even discrimination against each other. This workshop focuses on how people respond to stressful changes as well as effective strategies we can use to overcome anxiety and manage change in our lives.

With the dynamic changes of the Global Pandemic, work structures are rapidly changing, regardless of whether employees are equipped with skills to adapt and cope with the changes. Working together in this new norm can be challenging and frustrating because changes are not always easy. Come and learn the science behind our response to change and how best to cope and support others to enhance team engagement.

Anger is a common human response and emotion, and everyone has experienced anger to different degrees. These range from mild irritation to extreme rage. The emotion of anger is neither good nor bad. It is perfectly normal to experience it when people feel mistreated or wronged. What is important is how we deal with it. Uncontrolled anger of any quality possesses very destructive and negative consequences to both self and others. It affects personal relationships and one’s quality of life.

Stress can come from many areas, but the hardest one to battle is our own inner critic. Our personal expectations, judgments, and fears often impair us from overcoming challenges. A healthy mind enables us to vercome life’s distresses, grow in resilience and maintain mental and emotional stability. By cultivating a healthy mind, we grow in
self-awareness and understanding, and can build healthy relationships with others.

Stress is often viewed negatively because of the dire effects it has on our health. It is reported that stress is the basic cause of 60% of human ailments and disease. Despite this shocking fi gure, it is important to
realize that stress is inevitable and an essential part of life. There are even good stressors which prepare our body for further actions such as fight or flight. Instead of trying to avoid stress completely, this talk aims to impart tips on how to convert stresses to successes.

People from around the world revealed that they consider happiness and life satisfaction to be extremely  mportant, even more important than money. They are certainly not alone as these views are shared with a growing number of people looking for happiness in life and at work. Yet, most working adults in ingapore report not having positive experiences at work. Since most working adults spend a significant
amount of time working, experience at work can and will influence the quality of life and well-being of the individual.

Do ideas and thoughts seem to flood your mind sometimes? Are you feeling stressed at work? While we cannot avoid stress, there are strategies to help us cope better. Relaxation is a key to maintaining physical, mental, and emotional wellness. This talk explores mental relaxation techniques that can help put your mind and body at rest.

With the dynamic changes of the Global Pandemic, work structures are rapidly changing, regardless of whether companies of leaders are equipped with skills to adapt and cope with the changes. Managing
remote teams is becoming the new norm right now, and not all leaders are equipped in this area. What are the dynamics of effective teams? How to manage expectations and work performance when there is no facetime?

Most people spend at least one-third of their lives in the workplace. Amidst the hustle and bustle of workflow, productivity, and conquering deadlines, conflicts are bound to take place in varying frequencies and degrees. Conflict occurs when needs and expectations are misaligned, perspectives and values differ, or when communication breaks down. The fact that conflict exists, however, is not necessarily a bad thing; as long as it is resolved effectively, it can lead to personal and professional growth for all parties.

Even the best relationships can be challenging at times. Ironically, challenges are essential in a relationship so that people involved can grow closer together. However, some people fi nd the challenges too daunting and that their relationship could not recover from the damage. Often, these challenges arise out of miscommunication or the lack of communication between two individuals.

Success at work is no longer defi ned by the paycheck. It is also not about how smart an employee is, nor measured by the training or school one comes from. Companies around the world now place the emphasis on emotional intelligence. Companies value employees who can handle themselves and each other while working together. When things do not go our way, it is sometimes hard to accept leaving us with strong and negative emotions. While experiencing negative emotions is natural, it needs to be properly managed to avoid hurting others unnecessarily.

Class title: Cultivating Powerful Mindset for Achieving Goals
Class description: Some people call it perseverance, others call it grit. Whatever label you give, a strong mindset is a trait shared by high performing individuals, whether they are entrepreneurs, leaders, sports people or Olympians. Learning how to cultivate a strong mindset is a fundamental skill to develop resiliency against setbacks, and advance towards your goals.

When faced with the daunting idea of embarking on an exercise regime, some people fi nd it especially challenging to get into the swing of things due to negative internal thoughts about their ability to overcome the initial barrier or to maintain exercise involvement. This talk emphasizes the countering of negative self-talk using strategies based on Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, which strives to highlight the power of thoughts to affect motivation and ultimately, behavior. In addition, it aims to provide an insight to the types of motivation underlying physical activity and introduces key points to goal setting in order to equip individuals with the ability to create measurable and attainable targets for themselves. It’s time to get up and going!

Sleep is an intrinsic and extremely essential part of life; a fact that is often disregarded and devalued. Many individuals, especially those living in urban environments, make an ill-advised compromise on sleep, leaving them tired, sleepy, or unable to enjoy a restful night in the long term. This talk focuses on understanding the science of sleep, sleep problems and their respective causes and subsequent implications on health and daily life. Participants will be able to better understand the importance of
sleep, as well as learn how to implement healthy sleeping habits through various tips and the cultivation of healthy sleeping habits.

In our day-to-day lives, we encounter several different situations and it is inevitable to react with anxiety to some of them. However, it is important to differentiate ordinary anxiety from anxiety disorders.
This talk focuses on understanding the symptoms and factors that lead to the onset and maintenance of anxiety as well as effective strategies to overcome anxiety such as mental relaxation techniques, positive self-talk patterns, and overcoming cognitive distortions.

Class title: Live Well: Start with the End
Class description: How do you picture yourself in 20-30 years? Are you in good health and keeping well in that visualization? How do you ensure that you achieve that? Today, we spend over 40 hours per week for work and a bulk of the time juggling family or social commitments. We spend more time battling with deadlines and little to no time planning for our well-being. We often overlook that who we become in the future is dependent on who we are today. This talk will help you to jumpstart your plans to strengthen your well-being.

Most of the repetitive stress injuries suffered by office workers are a result of poor posture and poor setup of the work environment.
Common examples include neck pain, shoulder pain, back pain, tennis elbow, trigger finger, etc. Treatment of these injuries may be very
costly, especially if the root cause is not identified and rectified.

Class title: Ergonomics Workshop: Targeting Common Pains: Lower Back & Knees
Class description:
Most people feel back & knee pain is part and parcel of aging, with some even feeling the effects of an “aging spine” as young as 25, is that
a norm? When does it become a source of concern? These pains can even interfere with our daily lives and activities for e.g. spending time
with family outdoors, playing sports, or even as simple as walking. A pain-free lifestyle is the way to achieve sustainable fitness!

This talk lets you better understand your body and the current status of your health. Learn about Integrative Medicine and how it can help stamp out diseases before they develop. Update yourself on the latest modalities and what alternative medicine can do for you. With modern advances in natural medicine, a longer, better quality life is now possible with a holistic and non-invasive approach. 120 years old is the new 80!

Class title: Men & Women: Foreseeing Your Health in 10 years
Class description: You will learn the most common health issues of both genders, how to identify them, and how to prevent them. This talk takes you ten years from now to see where you will stand in terms of health and wellbeing.

Art Therapy is a technique that can foster healing and well-being. The purpose of Art Therapy is to help people to explore their self-expression while finding new ways to gain their personal insights and develop their new coping skills.
Gond Art is one of the many Art Therapies that is created out of carefully drawn lines. Lines are used in such a way to convey a sense of movement to still images. Dots and dashes are added to impart a greater sense of movement and increase the amount of detail. As this art form is tribal, Motifs used in this art are associated with forests and animals.

Imagine the experience of using handmade soap of your favourite scent, made using only natural raw ingredients of your choice and liking. In this workshop, you will get to learn how to make soap using the melt and pour method mixed with essential oils. The handmade soap does not contain any synthetic additives or any chemicals generally found in commercial soaps that could easily aggravate skin, causing major discomfort. Get ready to feel refreshed, moisturised and supple even after multiple washes.

Meridian Therapy focuses on the basic concept of the meridian system and its impact on our health. This is done by using various acupressure points with hand techniques such as kneading, tapping, and cupping, which increases the blood circulation and strengthens each individual's general well-being.

Happiness is associated with numerous outcomes including having better relationships, a successful career, and healthier life. Barbara Fredickson, a psychologist, supports that positive emotions have
long-lasting effects on a person’s growth and development. Positive emotions and laughter can protect us against negative emotions, enhance resilience, and improve overall well-being.
Relief stress and calm the nervous system through deep breathing techniques - let go of tensions on the physical, mental and emotional level
Keep the chaos away! Bring the mind to a place of stillness and “Drop in” to the calming beats of the drum to improve focus and concentration.

Immerse in beautiful sounds and vibrations that are healing for your body and mind. The sounds and vibrations affect the body at a cellular level since every organ and every cell in the body vibrates at a particular frequency. Deemed as the medicine of the future, the waves of sound in this class will trigger a relaxation response, leaving you feeling rested and relaxed.

In this session, we will look at how the practice of mindfulness can help bring calm and stability to our daily lives. We will be covering 3 positions - mindful eating, mindful walking, and mindful sitting. One should feel a sense of calmness and relaxedness after the session.

Most of our ill feelings arise because of closing ourselves off from others. The practice of loving-kindness helps to release tense and negative emotions, inviting positive heartwarming emotions for ourselves and the people around us. With a more open heart, we can navigate the world with more ease and less friction. Loving-kindness meditation can be an antidote if we constantly feel in conflict with others.

Being able to cope with stress is an important skill in the world today. In a stress management meditation session, one learns how to be comfortable with unpleasant feelings that arise daily. 2 positions will be explored in this session, namely standing and sitting. Regular practice of stress management meditation helps to build mental resilience.

Qi Gong meditation is a more dynamic form of meditation wherein participants are mostly standing and moving. Qi Gong meditation helps to release tension buildup in the body and at the same time provides mental relief. Regular practice of Qi Gong meditation helps to build a strong body to handle the daily rigors of life.
